<h4>Reconnect Guru</h4>

Reconnect Guru meditates on <code>udev</code> device connection events,
telling OctoPrint to reconnect the serial connection to the printer when a
suitable device is detected.

<div class="control-group">
    <label class="checkbox">
        <input type="checkbox"
               data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.enabled">
        Enable automatic reconnection
    </label>
</div>

<div class="control-group">
    <label>Connection delay after device detection (seconds)</label>
    <input type="number" min="0" class="input-small"
           data-bind="value: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.connect_delay_seconds">
    <p class="help-block">
        Time to wait after device is detected before attempting connection
    </p>
</div>

<h4>Device Filters</h4>
<p class="help-block">
    Leave filters empty to connect to any detected device.
    Specify filters to only connect to devices matching all specified criteria.
</p>

<div class="control-group">
    <label>Vendor ID (e.g., 1a86)</label>
    <input type="text" class="input-medium"
           data-bind="value: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.filter_vendor_id">
</div>

<div class="control-group">
    <label>Product ID (e.g., 7523)</label>
    <input type="text" class="input-medium"
           data-bind="value: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.filter_product_id">
</div>

<div class="control-group">
    <label>Serial Number</label>
    <input type="text" class="input-medium"
           data-bind="value: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.filter_serial">
</div>

<div class="control-group">
    <label>USB Port (e.g., 1.2 or 1.1.3)</label>
    <input type="text" class="input-medium"
           data-bind="value: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.filter_port">
    <p class="help-block">
        Match specific USB port on Raspberry Pi
    </p>
</div>

<h4>Other</h4>
<div class="control-group">
    <label class="checkbox">
        <input type="checkbox"
               data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.reconnect_guru.message_on_connect">
        Send M117 message on connect
    </label>
</div>
